President Biden is focused on responding to and aiding in the recovery efforts following Hurricane Fiona in Puerto Rico. He has expressed full support for Puerto Rico officials, first responders, and those affected by the storm. Prior to the hurricane's landfall, he approved an Emergency Declaration and quickly granted the Governor of Puerto Rico's request for a Major Disaster Declaration for Individual and Public Assistance. The President has been in regular communication with Governor Pierluisi and requested that FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell travel to the island. During a briefing in New York, President Biden announced additional financial support for Puerto Rico and pledged ongoing assistance in the recovery process. The Administration has taken swift action to ensure a well-coordinated federal response, including expediting power restoration and investing in long-term climate resilience.